    • Method Detail

      • addVar

        public ProxySnifferVar addVar(ProxySnifferVar proxySnifferVar)
                       throws ProxySnifferVarHandlerDupScopeException,
                              ProxySnifferVarHandlerInvNameException,
                              ProxySnifferVarHandlerKeywordException
        Adds a new var - duplicate names with different scopes are not allowed. However conversions from SCOPE_LOOP or from SCOPE_INNER_LOOP to SCOPE_USER are allowed.
        Parameters:
        proxySnifferVar - the variable to add
        Returns:
        the reference to the added var if the var is new or the reference to the old var in case of duplication.
        Throws:
        ProxySnifferVarHandlerDupScopeException
        ProxySnifferVarHandlerInvNameException
        ProxySnifferVarHandlerKeywordException

      • addVarWithMergeSupport

        public ProxySnifferVar addVarWithMergeSupport(ProxySnifferVar proxySnifferVar)
                                       throws ProxySnifferVarHandlerDupScopeException,
                                              ProxySnifferVarHandlerInvNameException,
                                              ProxySnifferVarHandlerKeywordException
        Adds a new var with Merge support - duplicate names with different scopes are not allowed. However conversions from SCOPE_LOOP or from SCOPE_INNER_LOOP to SCOPE_USER are allowed. In case of duplicate names with same scope and in case of valid conversions (from SCOPE_LOOP or from SCOPE_INNER_LOOP to SCOPE_USER), the Variable Assigners and Extractors are merged.
        Parameters:
        proxySnifferVar - the variable to add
        Returns:
        the reference to the added var if the var is new or the reference to the old var in case of duplication.
        Throws:
        ProxySnifferVarHandlerDupScopeException
        ProxySnifferVarHandlerInvNameException
        ProxySnifferVarHandlerKeywordException
